JOHANNESBURG – National Treasury's budget head, Michael Sachs has resigned. “National Treasury confirms the resignation of its Deputy Director-General: Budget Office, Michael Sachs. Mr Sachs has expressed his interest to serve the public sector in a different capacity,” National Treasury said in a statement. It’s been reported that Presidential interference in the free higher education saga is the reason. President Jacob Zuma is seeking around R40-billion to fund it, an amount many officials say is unaffordable. However, Treasury could not confirm Sach's resignation and said it would release an official statement later on Monday. President Jacob Zuma is seeking around R40-billion to fund it, an amount many officials say it's unaffordable. READ: Treasury DG confirms exit The rand has also taken a knock against the dollar. Treasury is still struggling to boost economic growth and cut back on government spending.  eNCA